{
  "texts": [
    "Just as item (E) terminates the list of what the man pumping water can be said to do, the further consequences of an act of offloading can be differentiated from those events that form part of its internal teleological microstructure.",
    "Consider again the different cases of putative cognitive extension introduced at the end of (§3.1).",
    "Working through a long-division problem, you animate resources that in themselves cannot generate the norm-constrained structure of cognition: you intentionally imbue them with this structure.",
    "This counts as a cognitive action attributable to you because of this structure and the role it plays in your cognitive routines.",
    "It counts as a cognitive action attributable to you because the way you generate this structure accords with the norms of rational agency on which Anscombe's 'why?' question depends."
  ]
}